      • getNativeMemorySize_bytes

        int getNativeMemorySize_bytes()
                       throws PspException
        Approximately how many bytes did target system provide to create this object? For instance, for an ldap server, this would be how much LDIF information is behind this user. This is used for measuring memory efficiency of caches and is optional.
        Returns:
        How many bytes the target system provided to create this object. -1: if you don't want the memory efficiency of pspng's caches to be calculated.
        Throws:
        PspException
